               <msContents>
                  <summary>The names of Mary in various languages (f. i r); Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a, ቅዳሴ፡ ማርያም፡ (f<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-36v); Image of Mary of Edom. መልክአ፡ ኤዶም. Chaîne, Répertoire 221 (f<locus target="#37r">37r, </locus>-39v); Asmat prayer (<locus target="#40v">40v</locus>)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="36v" facs="003">Fols 1r–36v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1099Anapho">ʾAkkʷateta qʷǝrbān
                                                  za-qǝddus Hǝryāqos za-hagara Bǝhnǝsā</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>The hand changes at <locus target="#11r" facs="013">fol. 11r</locus></note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from="37r" to="39v" facs="039">Fols 37r–39v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2940RepCh221">Malkǝʾ-hymn to Our
                                                  Lady Mary</title><incipit xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምኪ፡ በአምኃ።  <gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>written in a different hand</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
